Olori Anu, one of the wives of 81-year-old Alaafin of Oyo, Oba Lamidi Adeyemi, is a year older today as she shared some beautiful photos on her social media page. Alaafin of Oyo, Oba Lamidi Adeyemi III was born on the 15th of October 1938 and is the current Alaafin, (traditional ruler), of the town of Oyo a state in Nigeria. Lamidi Adeyemi succeeded Alaafin Gbadegesin Ladigbolu II in 1970, during the governorship of Colonel Robert Adeyinka Adebayo. He is married to Ayaba Abibat Adeyemi who is his first wife. He attends most events with her or with one of the twelve junior wives of which Olori Anu is one of them. READ ALSO VP Yemi Osinbajo, Dangote, Pastor Adeboye, others attend virtual 60th birthday thanksgiving service of Ogun state governor, Dapo Abiodun (photos) Olori Anu Adeyemi turns a year older today as the mum of two shared some new photos on her Instragram page to celebrate her birthday.